Etsy Sellers: Your deposit is on the way
text:
A friend notified me that Etsy is back to sending payments ontime.

"Hi there,

We wanted to let you know that we’ve processed your deposit that was originally scheduled for Friday, March 10, and you should receive your funds in your bank account soon.

We apologize for the inconvenience and want to provide additional details. We experienced a delay in issuing payments to some sellers related to the unexpected collapse of Silicon Valley Bank. Following the news, we immediately began working with our other payment partners to establish new technical processes to help us get you your funds as soon as possible. Our teams have been working around the clock to implement a solution, and we're pleased to report that we have begun processing deposits without further delay.

Thankfully, transactions on the Etsy marketplace were not impacted. Buyers were able to continue purchasing items they love from our wonderful global community of sellers.

Thank you again for your patience. As always, please feel free to reach out to our Help Center 24/7 with any questions you might have.

Thank you,

The Etsy Team"

Ask HN: How do you promote waitlist landing pages when you launch a new product?
text:
I'm building a new product for DevOps and software engineers. I prepared a fancy landing page to explain what it does and what users can get.

Meanwhile, exposing the landing page itself is really difficult. I cannot post self-promotion postings on Reddit, my Twitter account doesn't have enough followers, DMs are treated as spam. I feel frustration these days.

I know I need to do things that don't scale as an entrepreneur. But I don't know how I can do that when I cannot post the landing page on forums where our target audience is in.
